Fowl typhoid, United Kingdom
----------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 15 Nov 2013 from Dr Nigel Gibbens, Chief Veterinary Officer, Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, London, United Kingdom.

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification (final report)
Date of start of the event: 2 Sep 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 9 Sep 2013
Report date: 15 Nov 2013
Date submitted to OIE: 15 Nov 2013
Date event resolved: 12 Sep 2013
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 27 Nov 2012
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: _Salmonella gallinarum_
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (2)
Outbreak 1 (SG2013-1): Pomeroy, County Tyrone, Northern Ireland
Date of start of the outbreak: 2 Sep 2013
Outbreak status: Resolved (12 Sep 2013)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Birds / 6000 / 100 / 100 / 5900 / 0
Affected population: Commercial egg laying flock.

Outbreak 2 (SG2013-2): Pomeroy, County Tyrone, Northern Ireland
Date of start of the outbreak: 3 Sep 2013
Outbreak status: Resolved (12 Sep 2013)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Birds / 24 000 / 500 / 500 / 23 500 / 0
Affected population: Commercial egg laying flock. 3-shed unit with disease in one shed only. However, all birds on the site were destroyed.

Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 2
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Birds / 30 000 / 600 / 600 / 29 400 / 0
Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Birds / 2 percent / 2 percent / 100 percent / 100 percent
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: 2nd outbreak within 3 kilometers [1.9 miles] of 1st outbreak. Geographical coordinates of the affected establishments were anonymised by placing the coordinates on a public place. In this case the centre of the closest local village was chosen as geographical location of the actual holdings.

Control measures
Measures applied: No vaccination; No treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Agri-Food and Biosciences Institute (AFBI), Vet Sciences Division, Stormont (National laboratory) / Birds / bacteriological examination / 9 Sep 2013 / Positive
Agri-Food and Biosciences Institute (AFBI), Vet Sciences Division, Stormont (National laboratory) / Birds / serotyping / 9 Sep 2013 / Positive

Future Reporting: The event is resolved. No more reports will be submitted.

The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.

